---
import RuntimeSpine from "./RuntimeSpine.astro";
import TerminalProof from "./TerminalProof.astro";
---

<section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <div class="eyebrow"><span class="status-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> Developer Preview · supervised runtime</div>
      <div class="hero-title-row">
        <h1 id="hero-title">Supervised subagents and workflows for coding agents.</h1>
        <div class="hero-mark" aria-hidden="true">
          <img src="/brand/pixir-icon.svg" width="256" height="256" alt="" />
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="lead">
        Pixir is an Elixir/OTP harness for running agent work as supervised local
        sessions. Drive it from the CLI or ACP clients; Pixir owns subagent
        lifecycle, workflow outcomes, failures, timeouts, and replayable evidence
        without making the presenter the runtime.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="button primary" href="https://hex.pm/packages/pixir">Install from Hex</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="https://pixir.hexdocs.pm/readme.html">Read HexDocs</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="https://github.com/Ranvier-Technologies/pixir">View source</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-proof" role="group" aria-label="Pixir proof artifacts">
      <TerminalProof />
      <RuntimeSpine />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
